Acknowledges receipt of her letter. Begs her to tell her mama,<note>Clarissa Cattermole (1813-92).</note> that I have no knowledge of the copyright law in its reference to painting and engraving.<note>2Mrs Cattermole was presumably exploring possible sources of income from her husband’s work; a review of the Institute of Painters in Water-Colour exhibition, commenting unfavourably upon the work of Cattermole’s son, Charles, noted George Cattermole’s remaining works were to be dispersed by sale at auction (<hi rend="italic">The Times</hi>, 20 Feb 69).</note>
